Hey guys, let’s talk about Mental Health Awareness Month! It’s that time of year when we all come together to raise awareness about mental health and break down the stigma around mental illness. 

Mental health is just as important as physical health. Unfortunately, there’s still a lot of stigma and misunderstanding out there. But there’s help available! Hotlines, support groups, and therapy services are all great resources to get you started. And remember, it’s never too late to seek help. 

As someone who has been diagnosed with Bi-Polar disorder, I want to use my platform to share my story. 

I wanted to share my story because I think it’s so important for all of us to prioritize our mental health. It’s also important to check in with the people you care about, because you never know what someone might be going through. I know that I can sometimes put on a happy face at work and in social situations, but that doesn’t mean that everything is okay.

So, let’s all take some time this month to prioritize our mental health and to support those around us who might be struggling. We’re all in this together, and together, we can make a difference. Thank you for listening.
